==Founders==
Co-founders Matallana and Richards have both been diagnosed with fibromyalgia. They first met in 1997 through discussions in online [[fibromyalgia]] chat groups, and shared similar concerns over incorrect diagnoses as well as a lack of available information and patient support.<ref name="FDA1"/> Matallana had first experienced symptoms of pain and fatigue in 1993, and by 1997 had visited 37 doctors before being diagnosed with fibromyalgia.<ref name="UPI1">
 {{cite news   
 |url=http://www.upi.com/Science_News/2002/07/05/Fibromyalgia-may-be-on-the-increase/UPI-21871025885350/   
 |title=Fibromyalgia may be on the increase   
 |last=Mitchell   
 |first=Steve   
 |date=July 5, 2002   
 |publisher=[[United Press International]]   
 |accessdate=2009-07-20}}</ref><ref name="NYT2">
 {{cite news   
 |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/14/health/14pain.html?_r=1&ref=us   
 |title=Drug Approved. Is Disease Real?    
 |last=Berensen   
 |first=Alex   
 |date=January 14, 2008   
 |publisher=[[New York Times]]   
 |accessdate=2009-07-20}}</ref> Richards said that she had become ill in 1989, but did not receive a diagnosis of Fibromyalgia until 1996.<ref name="KLRBIO">
 {{cite web   
 |url=http://www.healthcentral.com/chronic-pain/c/5949/profile   
 |title=Karen Lee Richards bio   
 |work=healthcentral.com   
 |accessdate=2009-07-20}}</ref> After the two met, they organized gatherings with other fibromyalgia patients who wanted to increase public awareness of the issue, initiating the National Fibromyalgia Awareness Campaign,<ref name="AT1">
 {{cite news
 |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-323520_ITM
 |title=A long bike ride for the many who can't
 |last=Guthrie
 |first=Patricia
 |date=September 18, 1997
 |publisher=[[Albuquerque Tribune]]
 |accessdate=2009-07-20}}</ref><ref>
 {{cite web
 |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-529525_ITM
 |title=Questions and Answers About Fibromyalgia
 |date=December 1, 1999
 |publisher=[[National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases]]
 |accessdate=2009-07-20}}</ref> which developed over the following five years to become the NFA.<ref name="NFA1">
 {{cite web
 |url=http://www.fmaware.org/site/PageServer?pagename=about_nfa#history
 |title=NFA History
 |publisher=National Fibromyalgia Association
 |accessdate=2009-07-20}}</ref>  Matallana is past president of the NFA, having served through 2011 and is [[publisher]] and [[Editor-in-chief]] of ''Fibromyalgia AWARE'' magazine.<ref>
 {{cite web|url=http://www.prohealth.com/library/showarticle.cfm?id=6077&t=CFIDS_FM   
 |title=Q & A with Lynne Matallana, Founder of the National Fibromyalgia Association   
 |date=November 15, 2004   
 |publisher=Pro Health   
 |accessdate=2009-07-20}}</ref> Richards served as NFA's [[vice president]] from 1997 through 2006, and as executive editor of ''Fibromyalgia AWARE'' for four years after the magazine's 2002 launch.<ref name="KLRBIO" />

